'''''Section contains:''' Most sections added here will, obviously, contain content. However, it's possible to set "empty" headings for organizing. E.g., the page on chicken might have an empty, main heading called "Production", followed by sections for breeding, debeaking, etc. In the "Section contains" dropdown, you would then select "Heading only" for the Production section and "Content" for the subsections. Besides, the subsections should of course have a higher heading level.

'''''Section hosted at:''' If the section you're adding is only relevant locally, it should be hosted at this wiki ({{SITENAME}}). If the section is relevant in other countries, too, it should be hosted and translated at Atlas Global. To add such content, select "Atlas Global" from the "Section hosted at" menu '''and''' use the full pagename as section heading (i.e., as it appears on Atlas Global). For instance, <code>Chicken/Debeaking</code> is correct but <code>Debeaking</code> is not sufficient. Do '''not''' include the language part of the pagename (e.g., <code>/de</code>); language codes are set automatically.

